TITLE: Using JavaScript and CSS Coverage in Puppeteer
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use JavaScript and CSS coverage to calculate the percentage of initially executed code on a web page. It includes starting coverage, navigating to a page, stopping coverage, and calculating used bytes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/puppeteer/puppeteer/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-24.7.0/api/puppeteer.coverage.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
// Enable both JavaScript and CSS coverage
await Promise.all([
  page.coverage.startJSCoverage(),
  page.coverage.startCSSCoverage(),
]);
// Navigate to page
await page.goto('https://example.com');
// Disable both JavaScript and CSS coverage
const [jsCoverage, cssCoverage] = await Promise.all([
  page.coverage.stopJSCoverage(),
  page.coverage.stopCSSCoverage(),
]);
let totalBytes = 0;
let usedBytes = 0;
const coverage = [...jsCoverage, ...cssCoverage];
for (const entry of coverage) {
  totalBytes += entry.text.length;
  for (const range of entry.ranges) usedBytes += range.end - range.start - 1;
}
console.log(`Bytes used: ${(usedBytes / totalBytes) * 100}%`);
```

