TITLE: Using Page.waitForFrame with a Predicate Function in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use `page.waitForFrame` with an asynchronous predicate function in TypeScript. The function checks if a frame's underlying element has a `name` attribute equal to 'test'. It waits until such a frame appears and assigns it to the `frame` variable.
SOURCE: https://github.com/puppeteer/puppeteer/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-24.7.0/api/puppeteer.page.waitforframe.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
const frame = await page.waitForFrame(async frame => {
  const frameElement = await frame.frameElement();
  if (!frameElement) {
    return false;
  }
  const name = await frameElement.evaluate(el => el.getAttribute('name'));
  return name === 'test';
});
```

