TITLE: Finding and Logging the Focused Node in Accessibility Tree
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to find the focused node in the accessibility tree and log its name, using a recursive helper function to traverse the tree structure.
SOURCE: https://github.com/puppeteer/puppeteer/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-24.7.0/api/puppeteer.accessibility.snapshot.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const snapshot = await page.accessibility.snapshot();
const node = findFocusedNode(snapshot);
console.log(node && node.name);

function findFocusedNode(node) {
  if (node.focused) return node;
  for (const child of node.children || []) {
    const foundNode = findFocusedNode(child);
    return foundNode;
  }
  return null;
}
```

