TITLE: Using ElementHandle.waitForSelector in Puppeteer
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to use the waitForSelector method to detect when an image appears on various websites. The code navigates through different URLs and logs when the first image is found on any of the pages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/puppeteer/puppeteer/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-24.7.0/api/puppeteer.elementhandle.waitforselector.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import puppeteer from 'puppeteer';

(async () => {
  const browser = await puppeteer.launch();
  const page = await browser.newPage();
  let currentURL;
  page
    .mainFrame()
    .waitForSelector('img')
    .then(() => console.log('First URL with image: ' + currentURL));

  for (currentURL of [
    'https://example.com',
    'https://google.com',
    'https://bbc.com',
  ]) {
    await page.goto(currentURL);
  }
  await browser.close();
})();
```

